adjectives.description: tanklike (comparative more tanklike, superlative most tanklike)

entries.meaning: Resembling or characteristic of a tank (military vehicle).
examples: The mechanical digger had tanklike treads.

entries.meaning: Resembling or characteristic of a tank (container).
examples: Yes, Rex had “got that,” and the old man was a great sport, but when he said a thing he meant it—otherwise Rex would never have been moving slowly up and down like a large fish in the dim green waters of this vast tanklike hall.
